WEBVTT

00:04:29.575 --> 00:04:31.614
really does seem to have been a foundation

00:04:31.638 --> 00:04:33.159
of so much of what you've done

00:04:33.183 --> 00:04:37.037
because many people go through life
with quite a simple picture of humans.

00:04:37.061 --> 00:04:41.790
Talk about what that traditional view
of human nature has been,

00:04:41.814 --> 00:04:43.425
especially even in economics.

00:04:43.449 --> 00:04:47.308
DK: Well, there are many versions
of "what makes humans think."

00:04:47.976 --> 00:04:51.977
A particular version is the foundation
of the science of economics

00:04:52.001 --> 00:04:55.777
and the so-called rational agent model.

00:04:56.314 --> 00:05:00.567
The assumption's
that economic agents are rational.